  "vanillaAliases": ["vanilla", "base", "v", "game", "starbound", "sb", "original", "official"],
  "vanillaTips": [
    "Click [LMB] while holding a weapon for default attack.",
    "Hold [Shift] while arranging blocks to place them in a precise grid.",
    "Hold [Ctrl] and drag your Mouse to look around.",
    "Hold [Alt] to highlight interactables and living forms nearby.",
    "Pressing [A] or [D] allows you to move horizontally. Try not to go rounds on a planet.",
    "Water puts out burning status effects. Keep some in quick access.",
    "Don't forget to eat.",
    "Sleeping heals you over time for free.",
    "You can dual-wield flashlights and one-handed weapons to explore dark caves safely.",
    "Upgrade your Matter Manipulator's fluid collection early to easily gather poison and lava.",
    "The broken broadsword can be upgraded later. Keep it safe in your storage.",
    "Pixels are lost upon death in all modes, but the amount depends on your difficulty.",
    "Need fuel? Moons are rich in Erchius, but beware the unknown entity.",
    "Double-handed weapons usually deal more damage than one-handed ones.",
    "Ingredients can be combined at a Kitchen Counter to make powerful buff foods.",
    "You can beam up to your ship from deep underground on Casual difficulty.",
    "Hoverbikes are excellent for traversing large planetary surfaces with style.",
    "Flags act as teleportation bookmarks. Place them deep underground for fast trips.",
    "Сertain merchant inventories change daily. Check back often for new assortments.",
    "Throwing glowsticks or flares down deep shafts is a great way to check for deadly drops.",
    "Tenant rent scales with the danger level of the planet they live on. Build colonies on dangerous worlds for better loot.",
    "Mechs may provide you comfort. Or become your biggest curse.",
    "Bandages and medkits are incompatible as they serve different purposes in a tough encounter; keep both handy.",
    "To defeat an eldritch evil, shoot at it until it dies.",
    "There is no shame in abandoning your mission if you are scared, the galaxy will wait.",
	"Were you a pirate in your past life? The universe remembers everything. Use the coordinates to visit your former treasure planet.",
	"Were you the Sun in your past life? Rumor has it - before it was cool.",
    "Keep a clear escape route when exploring dangerous areas.",
    "Use more rope. Carefully repelling down cliffs is much safer than leaping blindly.",
    "Meteors fall fast and hit hard. Maintain a thick roof above your head if you see some.",
    "Ducking with a shield can briefly block all sorts of laser beams.",
    "Speed rules melee. Keep moving to avoid getting cornered, and not only by native fauna.",
    "Don't walk around with an open inventory in unknown territory.",
    "If your health reaches zero, you will die.",
    "Lava is hot. Swimming in it is strongly discouraged.",
    "Fall damage is the number one cause of death for careless explorers.",
    "Remember to occasionally reward your pets with treats.",
    "You can play musical instruments to pass the time while your friends do all the mining.",
    "Always carry a stack of blocks. You never know when you'll need to box yourself in.",
    "Bows and hunting spears cause monsters to drop meat and parts.",
    "In a pinch, a campfire provides a tiny amount of light.",
    "Don't poke the Poptops.",
	"Weep not, my child.",
    "You can catch bugs with a Bug Net. Gotta catch 'em all!",
    "Fossils can be carefully excavated with Fossil Brushes. It requires perseverance.",
    "Salves may be slow. Be patient.",
    "Painting blocks with the Paint Tool is a way to customize your builds.",
    "Wiring Tool lets you create sort of logic circuits when applied to some special objects. Just try it on paper first.",
    "Monsters on high-tier planets have deadlier attacks and unique abilities.",
    "You can capture monsters using Capture Pods. Weaken them first!",
    "Healing water can be found on certain planets and bring you back on feet.",
    "Poison can be weaponized if you're creative, but it mostly hurts you and your crewmates.",
    "Infinity Express at the Outpost has everything an aspiring adventurer needs, provided you have enough pixels.",
    "Scanning items in the world teaches your Pixel Printer how to replicate them.",
    "Crew members can provide useful buffs both on your ship and in the field.",
    "Medics just gonna heal you, while Chemists provide useful stats.",
    "Do Yellow Chemists dream of glowing ship?",
    "Engineers and Mechanics improve your ship's fuel efficiency and capacity.",
    "Penguin mercenaries can be hired at the Beakeasy with dubloons.",
    "Sprinklers automate farming by watering crops for you.",
    "Mooshis produce milk. Hens lay eggs. Do you feel like a farmer yet?",
    "Moth Traps provide silk, useful for different armor.",
    "You need a Breathing EPP to survive in space.",
    "Radiation EPPs protect you from radioactive planets.",
    "Cooling EPPs are necessary for fiery stars.",
    "You can apply Augments to your EPP for extra stats, like glowing in the dark or moving faster.",
    "Ice weapons can slow enemies down, giving you breathing room.",
    "Grenade launchers can shoot bouncing grenades. Use space to your advantage.",
    "Some swords have a parry ability. Time it right to negate damage.",
    "Hammers have a massive windup but deal incredible damage and knockback.",
    "Throwables can be held out to keep enemies at bay.",
    "Dual-wield daggers for some real frenzy.",
    "Boomerangs return to you. Catch them to attack faster.",
    "Chakrams can hover in place while dealing some damage.",
    "Vehicles can be repaired at the Outpost with auto chips.",
    "Boats are great for exploring oceanic planets without getting wet.",
    "You can try to upgrade your weapons at an Ancient Anvil in Vaults.",
    "Ancient Vaults are challenges meant for heavily armed explorers.",
    "Essence is used to terraform planets and upgrade weapons.",
    "Challenge Doors offer obstacle сourses or combat arenas for rare loot.",
    "Don't dig straight down. This isn't Craftmine, but it's still a bad idea.",
    "If it glows, it's either valuable or highly radioactive.",
    "You can sit in chairs. It doesn't do much, but you can so.",
    "Not closing doors in front of you is basic galatic etiquette. Such a pity if your crewmates think otherwise.",
    "If you are reading this, Starbound is still loading."
  ],
