    "Frackin' Universe": {
	  "aliases": ["fu"],
      "checkPath": "/objects/crafting/fu_upgradetable/fu_upgradetable.object",
      "tips": [
        "Unsure how to get a particular material in bulk? Remember to review your lab directory; even rare materials can be easy to obtain if you know where to source them, which the directory will tell you.",
        "They say the Ancients aren't the only long dead race out there... Pay attention to when your SAIL tells you an anomaly has been detected on a planet. You might find something interesting there.",
        "Erchius isn't the only fuel you can use to power your FTL drive! If you are ever low on fuel, try using radioactive isotopes or hydrogen. The latter can be found in great quantities on a certain gacious planet...",
        "If you are ever unsatisfied with your species' traits, or they become a liability for exploring certain planet types, remember that they can be toggled on or off at a ship's SAIL terminal.",
        "The Science Outpost hosts a great deal of shops and quest-givers. Remember to check in from time-to-time to see what it's denizens have to offer. Just make sure to avoid Kevin...",
        "Don't be afraid to explore environments you aren't familiar with. Sometimes they can be survived without protection, or even be helpful. And if it does prove lethal? Well, you learned something.",
        "Being crazy is great! Madness increases the speed at which research is accumulated, and it can be used to develop new and exciting technology. Just be aware of the negative impact it can have on your health.",
        "Never throw away common materials! Resources like sulphur, coal, copper, water, or lead aren't exactly exciting, but you'll need a lot of them to make more exotic components.",
        "What are you doing with that old Matter Manipulator? Research into engineering to build better Manipulators, or build an upgradable mining laser. The sooner, the better!",
        "Don't be afraid to try something wild! The universe is a vast place, and it rewards experimentation and exploration. Learning is your greatest tool.",
        "Don't be daunted by all there is to learn. It's part of the fun, and once you figure it out, it'll become second-nature!"
      ]
    }
